        <hl1>Fort Lauderdale</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Alice T Friedman letter on Daisann McLane's April 9 travel article on Fort Lauderdale, Fla, notes excellent art collection at Museum of Art</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: I was surprised by the omission of the Museum of Art, Fort Lauderdale, www.museumofart.org. The museum has an excellent permanent collection and offers world-class special exhibitions. The author could have seen ''Impressionism to the Present: Camille Pissarro and His Descendants,'' since closed, and ''Willem de Kooning: In Process,'' still on view. And the museum has a relatively low general admission price, $10 for adults in summer; $12 the rest of the year.</p>
        <p>ALICE T. FRIEDMAN  Wellesley, Mass.</p>
      </block>
